§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Given a probability space $(Ω, ℱ, 𝗣)$, a sequence of $𝒢_1,
    …, 𝒢_n$ of sub-$σ$-algebras of $ℱ$, are ❬independent❭ if
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \textstyle ⦉

      ‖ 𝗣(A_1 ∩ A_2 ∩ ⋯ ∩ A_n) = ∏_{i = 1}^{n} 𝗣(A_i) ⦉
    ⦉
    for any $A_1 ∈ 𝒢_1$, $A_2 ∈ 𝒢_2$, $…$, $A_n ∈ 𝒢_n$. ⦉

  ‖ A family $\set{𝒢_i}_{i ∈ I}$ is a family of sub-$σ$-algebras
    of $ℱ$ is ❬independent❭ if any finitely many of them are
    independent. ⦉
⦉

